I"£<p>After serveral months of revision for the Tesla Cybertruck model, Tesla's CEO, Elon Musk announced that the design is finalized and he updated the timeline to production for mid 2023.</p>

<p>When they annouced the Cybertruck back in 2019, it was also announced that it would make the market by 2021. Due to Covid and other compilcations they first delayed the mass production of the car for 2022.</p>

<p>In early 2022 it was confirmed that Tesla again, plans to complete the Cybertruck's development and begin mass production in 2023.</p>

<p>During a recent interview with the Tesla Owners Club, Elon confirmed that the Cybertruck's design is now "locked" and ready for mass production.</p>

<blockquote>We need to get on that [getting the Cybertruck to production]. At least, the design is finally locked. We got too carried away [with design updates].</blockquote>

<p><img class="img-fluid" src="https://cdn.motor1.com/images/mgl/zxgAJq/s1/tesla-cyber-truck-on-track-4k-source-chile-al100.webp" alt="Demo Image" /></p>

<p>Musk has previously said that Tesla updated the Cybertruck with rear-wheel-steering and made several design changes.</p>

<p>Unfortunately due to the global crysis, and therefore chip shortage, Tesla woulnd't be able to mass produce the Cybertruck this year. Musk updated the product timeline for the Cybertruck to mid-2023.</p>

<p>Earlier this year, Cybertruck prototypes were spotted in the public, being tested by Tesla as well as being used for promotion at certain events.</p>

